#. <section class="sutta" id="sn8.5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn8.5:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn8.5:0.2"
msgid "1. Vaṅgīsavagga"
msgstr "1. With Vaṅgīsa"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn8.5:0.3"
msgid "5. Subhāsitasutta"
msgstr "5. Well-Spoken Words"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.5:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn8.5:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn8.5:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn8.5:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn8.5:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.189"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.407"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.5:2.1"
msgid "“Catūhi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgatā vācā subhāsitā hoti, no dubbhāsitā; anavajjā ca ananuvajjā ca viññūnaṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, speech that has four factors is well spoken, not poorly spoken. It’s blameless and is not criticized by sensible people."

msgctxt "sn8.5:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi catūhi?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn8.5:2.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu subhāsitaṃyeva bhāsati no dubbhāsitaṃ, dhammaṃyeva bhāsati no adhammaṃ, piyaṃyeva bhāsati no appiyaṃ, saccaṃyeva bhāsati no alikaṃ."
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant speaks well, not poorly; they speak on the teaching, not against the teaching; they speak pleasantly, not unpleasantly; and they speak truthfully, not falsely."

msgctxt "sn8.5:2.4"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi aṅgehi samannāgatā vācā subhāsitā hoti, no dubbhāsitā, anavajjā ca ananuvajjā ca viññūnan”ti."
msgstr "Speech with these four factors is well spoken, not poorly spoken. It’s blameless and is not criticized by sensible people.”"

msgctxt "sn8.5:2.5"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn8.5:2.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.5:3.1"
msgid "“Subhāsitaṃ uttamamāhu santo,"
msgstr "“Good people say that well-spoken words are foremost;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:3.2"
msgid "Dhammaṃ bhaṇe nādhammaṃ taṃ dutiyaṃ;"
msgstr "second, speak on the teaching, not against it;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:3.3"
msgid "Piyaṃ bhaṇe nāppiyaṃ taṃ tatiyaṃ,"
msgstr "third, speak pleasantly, not unpleasantly;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:3.4"
msgid "Saccaṃ bhaṇe nālikaṃ taṃ catutthan”ti."
msgstr "and fourth, speak truthfully, not falsely.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.5:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vaṅgīso uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Vaṅgīsa got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said:"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn8.5:4.2"
msgid "“paṭibhāti maṃ, bhagavā, paṭibhāti maṃ, sugatā”ti."
msgstr "“I feel inspired to speak, Blessed One! I feel inspired to speak, Holy One!”"

#. </p><p class="added">
msgctxt "sn8.5:4.3"
msgid "“Paṭibhātu taṃ, vaṅgīsā”ti bhagavā avoca."
msgstr "“Then speak as you feel inspired,” said the Buddha."

msgctxt "sn8.5:4.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vaṅgīso bhagavantaṃ sammukhā sāruppāhi gāthāhi abhitthavi:"
msgstr "Then Vaṅgīsa extolled the Buddha in his presence with fitting verses:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.5:5.1"
msgid "“Tameva vācaṃ bhāseyya,"
msgstr "“Speak only such words"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:5.2"
msgid "yāyattānaṃ na tāpaye;"
msgstr "as do not hurt yourself"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:5.3"
msgid "Pare ca na vihiṃseyya,"
msgstr "nor harm others;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:5.4"
msgid "sā ve vācā subhāsitā."
msgstr "such speech is truly well spoken."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.408"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.5:6.1"
msgid "Piyavācaṃva bhāseyya,"
msgstr "Speak only pleasing words,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:6.2"
msgid "yā vācā paṭinanditā;"
msgstr "words gladly welcomed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:6.3"
msgid "Yaṃ anādāya pāpāni,"
msgstr "Pleasing words are those"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:6.4"
msgid "paresaṃ bhāsate piyaṃ."
msgstr "that bring nothing bad to others."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.5:7.1"
msgid "Saccaṃ ve amatā vācā,"
msgstr "Truth itself is the undying word:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:7.2"
msgid "esa dhammo sanantano;"
msgstr "this is an ancient principle."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:7.3"
msgid "Sacce atthe ca dhamme ca,"
msgstr "Good people say that the teaching and its meaning"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:7.4"
msgid "āhu santo patiṭṭhitā."
msgstr "are grounded in the truth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn8.5:8.1"
msgid "Yaṃ buddho bhāsate vācaṃ,"
msgstr "The words spoken by the Buddha"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:8.2"
msgid "khemaṃ nibbānapattiyā;"
msgstr "for realizing the sanctuary, extinguishment,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:8.3"
msgid "Dukkhassantakiriyāya,"
msgstr "for making an end of suffering:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn8.5:8.4"
msgid "sā ve vācānamuttamā”ti."
msgstr "this really is the best kind of speech.”"
